# CollabCode — Full Project Context

> **Last updated:** 2026-03-05
> This document is the canonical source of truth for any agent working on this project.

---

## 1. Project Overview

**CollabCode** is a real-time collaborative code editor (think Google Docs for code). Two repos:

| Repo | Path | Stack |
|------|------|-------|
| **Backend** | `c:\Users\adity\Projects\collabcode-backend` | Node.js, Express, Prisma (PostgreSQL), Socket.IO, TypeScript |
| **Frontend** | `c:\Users\adity\Projects\collabcode-ui` | Next.js 14 (App Router), React, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, Monaco Editor |

**Env vars:**
- Backend: `DATABASE_URL`, `JWT_ACCESS_SECRET`, `JWT_REFRESH_SECRET`, `CLIENT_URL`, `PORT`
- Frontend: `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` (default `http://localhost:4000`)

---

## 2. Backend Architecture

### 2.1 Database Schema (`prisma/schema.prisma`)

| Model | Key Fields | Notes |
|-------|-----------|-------|
| `SubscriptionPlan` | `name`, `maxRooms`, `maxMembersPerRoom`, `maxJoinedRooms`, `chatRetentionDays`, `maxActiveSessions` | Seeded: Free plan |
| `User` | `email` (unique), `passwordHash`, `displayName`, `avatarUrl?`, `planId`, `createdAt` | Linked to plan |
| `Room` | `name`, `language`, `isPublic`, `ownerId`, `createdAt` | Has memberships, messages, document, invites |
| `RoomMembership` | `userId`, `roomId`, `role` (OWNER/MEMBER), `joinedAt` | Unique on [userId, roomId] |
| `RoomInvite` | `roomId`, `tokenHash`, `expiresAt`, `createdBy` | Token is hashed |
| `CodeDocument` | `roomId` (unique), `content` (Text), `version` (Int) | One per room |
| `Message` | `content`, `roomId`, `userId`, `createdAt` | Indexed by [roomId, createdAt DESC] |
| `RefreshToken` | `tokenHash`, `userId`, `expiresAt` | Multiple per user |

### 2.2 REST API Routes

**Auth** (`/api/v1/auth`):
| Method | Path | Auth | Description |
|--------|------|------|-------------|
| POST | `/register` | No | Register → returns `accessToken`, sets refresh cookie |
| POST | `/login` | No | Login → returns `accessToken`, sets refresh cookie |
| POST | `/refresh` | Cookie | Refresh access token |
| POST | `/logout` | Cookie | Revoke current refresh token |
| POST | `/logout-all` | Bearer | Revoke all refresh tokens for user |
| GET | `/me` | Bearer | Get user profile with plan details |

**Rooms** (`/api/v1/rooms`):
| Method | Path | Auth | Description |
|--------|------|------|-------------|
| POST | `/` | Bearer | Create room (name, language, isPublic?) |
| GET | `/dashboard` | Bearer | Get owned, joined, public rooms |
| POST | `/join-by-invite` | Bearer | Join via invite token |
| GET | `/:id` | Bearer | Get room details |
| DELETE | `/:id` | Bearer | Delete room (owner only) |
| POST | `/:id/join` | Bearer | Join public room |
| POST | `/:id/invite` | Bearer | Create invite link (owner only) |
| GET | `/:id/members` | Bearer | List room members |
| DELETE | `/:id/members/:userId` | Bearer | Remove member (owner only) |
| GET | `/:id/messages` | Bearer | Get room messages |

### 2.3 Socket.IO Events

**Authentication:** Token sent via `socket.handshake.auth.token`, verified as JWT.

**Client → Server:**
| Event | Payload | Description |
|-------|---------|-------------|
| `room:join` | `roomId: string` | Join room, get initial document state |
| `room:leave` | `roomId: string` | Leave room |
| `room:edit` | `{ roomId, patch, version }` | Send full document snapshot |
| `room:chat` | `{ roomId, content }` | Send chat message |
| `room:cursor` | `{ roomId, cursor: { line, ch } }` | Send cursor position |

**Server → Client:**
| Event | Payload | Description |
|-------|---------|-------------|
| `room:joined` | `{ roomId, document, version, participants }` | Initial room state |
| `room:presence` | `{ participants }` | Updated participant list |
| `room:edit` | `{ roomId, patch, version, userId }` | Broadcast edit to others (via `socket.to()`) |
| `room:resync` | `{ roomId, document, version }` | Full resync on version mismatch |
| `room:new-message` | `ChatMessage` | New chat message |
| `room:cursor-update` | `{ userId, cursor }` | Cursor position update |
| `room:kicked` | `{ roomId }` | User was removed |
| `error` | `{ event, message }` | Error response |

> **Critical:** Server uses `socket.to(room)` for `room:edit`, which excludes the sender. The sender must optimistically increment `versionRef` after emitting.

### 2.4 Backend File Structure

```
src/
├── app.ts                  # Express app setup (cors, cookie-parser, routes)
├── server.ts               # HTTP server + Socket.IO init
├── config/env.ts           # Environment config with zod validation
├── controllers/
│   ├── auth.controller.ts  # Auth route handlers
│   └── room.controller.ts  # Room route handlers
├── middleware/
│   ├── authenticate.ts     # JWT Bearer auth middleware
│   ├── validate.ts         # Zod validation middleware
│   └── errorHandler.ts     # Global error handler
├── routes/
│   ├── auth.routes.ts      # Auth route definitions
│   ├── room.routes.ts      # Room route definitions (all behind authenticate)
│   └── index.ts            # Route aggregator
├── services/
│   ├── auth.service.ts     # Auth business logic (register, login, refresh, etc.)
│   ├── room.service.ts     # Room CRUD, dashboard, invites, members
│   └── message.service.ts  # Message persistence
├── sockets/
│   ├── index.ts            # Socket.IO init + auth middleware
│   ├── room.handler.ts     # room:join/leave/chat/cursor handlers
│   ├── editor.handler.ts   # room:edit handler (version check, resync)
│   └── room-store.ts       # In-memory active rooms store
├── types/express.d.ts      # Express request type augmentation
└── utils/
    ├── jwt.ts              # JWT sign/verify helpers
    ├── hash.ts             # bcrypt + crypto hash helpers
    ├── ApiError.ts         # Custom API error class
    └── asyncHandler.ts     # Express async error wrapper
```

