## 5. Current State & Known Issues

### What Works
- ✅ Auth flow (register, login, logout, auto-refresh)
- ✅ Dashboard with real API data (owned/joined/public rooms)
- ✅ Create room modal → API → dashboard refresh
- ✅ Room view with Monaco editor + real-time document sync
- ✅ Bidirectional chat with auto-scroll
- ✅ Participant presence via socket
- ✅ Share modal with invite link + copy + expiry
- ✅ Room Settings modal (room info, leave, delete with confirmation)
- ✅ Connection state UI (connecting spinner, reconnecting banner, error overlay)
- ✅ Profile page with plan stats
- ✅ Plans/pricing page with 3 tiers
- ✅ Sidebar with Profile, Pricing, Rooms, clickable logo
- ✅ TopBar user dropdown (Profile, Room Settings, Log out)
- ✅ Download button in TopBar
- ✅ Auth page mode from URL query params (`?mode=signup`)
- ✅ Privacy, Terms, 404 pages

### Known Issues / Incomplete
- ⚠️ Sidebar "Settings" link is still `href="#"` (no settings page exists)
- ⚠️ Profile "Active Sessions" stat shows plan limit (`maxActiveSessions`), not actual active session count
- ⚠️ Participant list in room only shows display name for current user; others show "User 1", "User 2" (socket only sends `userId`, not `displayName`)
- ⚠️ Download button in TopBar is wired but handler behavior not yet implemented
- ⚠️ Landing page navbar still shows "Sign Up" / "Log In" even when user is authenticated

### Constraints (User-Defined)
- **No backend modifications** — all changes must be frontend-only
- **No UI redesign** — maintain existing layout and visual style
- **No feature expansion** — no file tree, git, debugger, search, terminal, friends, notifications
- **No console.log** — production-standard code
- **No placeholder content** — everything must use real data

